statement.p:
Rewrite the following without summation sign for n = 3. It is not necessary that you understand or expand the notation \left(
           \begin{array}{c}
           n \\
           k \\
           \end{array}
           \right) at this point.
         (x + y)^n= \sum_{k=0}^n \left(
           \begin{array}{c}
           n \\
           k \\
           \end{array}
           \right)x^{n-k}y^k.
